HEADWORD: Polemics
<hw>Po*lem"ics</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>pol⟦eacute⟧mique</ets>.]</ety> <def>The art or practice of
disputation or controversy, especially on religious subjects; that
branch of theological science which pertains to the history or conduct
of ecclesiastical controversy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

